Derrick Spies, News24 correspondentSA Police. (Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Port Elizabeth - A 95-year-old woman has been found murdered in her home in Uitenhage.Police spokesperson Sergeant Majola Nkohli said the victim could not be named at this stage as there was a suspicion that she had also been raped during the incident. Nkohli said a neighbour, who had been bringing food over for the elderly woman, found her body on the floor in the lounge of a house in Luyt Street, Uitenhage, around 17:30 on Thursday afternoon. He said the woman appeared to have been strangled with a telephone cord.The motive remained unknown and nothing appeared to be missing from the house. Police are urging anyone with information to contact the investigating officer Warrant Officer Jacques Nel - of the Uitenhage police on 041 996 4581. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.